02:31:50,810 --> 02:31:54,052
[SPEAKER_15]: I carefully wrote down answers to all the questions I received ahead of time.

1825
02:31:55,240 --> 02:32:01,744
[SPEAKER_15]: I'm actually delighted that you went off book because I feel a lot more comfortable answering the questions like this than trying to figure out should I read it, should I answer it?

1826
02:32:02,165 --> 02:32:02,525
[SPEAKER_15]: Thank you.

1827
02:32:07,788 --> 02:32:10,050
[SPEAKER_15]: I think I'll just read my closing statement, if that's okay.

1828
02:32:11,651 --> 02:32:13,412
[SPEAKER_15]: I see government service as a relay race.

1829
02:32:13,933 --> 02:32:20,217
[SPEAKER_15]: You take the baton from the person before you, do your best to improve it while you have it, then make a clean pass to the person after you.

1830
02:32:21,309 --> 02:32:23,470
[SPEAKER_15]: I was lucky to get such a great pass from Jim Connery.

1831
02:32:23,850 --> 02:32:25,711
[SPEAKER_15]: He showed me the wisdom of succession planning.

1832
02:32:27,192 --> 02:32:29,533
[SPEAKER_15]: You've been very fortunate with Superintendent Belson.

1833
02:32:30,093 --> 02:32:32,534
[SPEAKER_15]: You have a fiscally stable, well-run district.

1834
02:32:32,974 --> 02:32:35,635
[SPEAKER_15]: It will be very difficult to replace him once he retires.

1835
02:32:36,796 --> 02:32:39,137
[SPEAKER_15]: There is no substitute for knowledgeable experience.

1836
02:32:40,077 --> 02:32:42,158
[SPEAKER_15]: But I can help with the transition to new leadership.

1837
02:32:42,839 --> 02:32:50,522
[SPEAKER_15]: Since your existing systems function appropriately right now, I can take the time to build relationships around the district and learn as much as I can from everyone.

1838
02:32:51,330 --> 02:32:56,075
[SPEAKER_15]: I can begin the process of holding institutional memory and become a resource to those who come later.

1839
02:32:57,116 --> 02:33:04,303
[SPEAKER_15]: With my mix of urban and suburban experience, I bring a background that will be sensitive to the cultural diversity and unique needs of Medford.

1840
02:33:05,024 --> 02:33:10,249
[SPEAKER_15]: I would welcome the opportunity to work with Superintendent Belson, his administrative team, and all of you.

1841
02:33:11,270 --> 02:33:14,273
[SPEAKER_15]: I hope that you'll choose me to be your next Director of Finance and Administration.

1842
02:33:15,274 --> 02:33:15,534
[SPEAKER_15]: Thank you.

